                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/1341: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-01T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 1, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Your despatch No. 796, February 19, page 12. The Department feels that the
                    original of the Act of Capitulation should not be held in the archives of the
                    Legation and that it should be transmitted to the Costa Rican Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
